For rice sowing and fertilizer placement, I recommend the following methods:
Select 25-30 days old seedlings for transplanting;
Fertilizer placement: Use 18 kg of urea, 17 kg of diammonium phosphate and 9 kg of potassium chloride per acre. Urea is applied in two times, the first time during soil preparation and the second time 30-50 days after transplanting. Fertilization time 3-4 days before transplanting. The above methods can help you achieve good rice growth.

The a.i. question refers to the problem of artificial insemination of calves. Artificial insemination is a common reproductive technique that occurs by injecting frozen semen into the reproductive tract of a cow. When performing artificial insemination, you need to pay attention to the following points:
Choose high-quality frozen semen;
Ensure hygiene and safety when injecting semen;
Select the appropriate time for artificial insemination, usually during the best time of the calf's estrus;
During the artificial insemination process, attention needs to be paid to details to ensure correct operation and no damage;
Use appropriate equipment and tools to ensure successful artificial insemination.
Through these measures, the success rate of artificial insemination can be improved and the reproduction of calves can be promoted.

Methods of raising fish include the following aspects:
Select appropriate fish species based on their living habits and breeding conditions;
Provide appropriate water quality and environment, including water temperature, pH value, dissolved oxygen, etc.;
Feed rationally and provide appropriate feed according to the needs of fish, including plankton, fish meal, fish oil, etc.;
Clean the fish tank or pond regularly to keep the water clean;
Regularly check the health status of fish and take timely measures if there are any abnormalities;
According to the growth and development stage of fish, adjust feeding management, including feed type and feeding frequency.
Through these feeding methods, the growth rate and health status of fish can be improved and the smooth progress of breeding can be ensured.

When harvesting rice, you can take the following steps:
1. Use a sickle or cutting knife to cut off the rice ears;
2. Bundle the harvested rice into bundles and place them in drying yards or other appropriate places to dry;
3. After the rice is completely dry, use a threshing machine or other tools to separate the rice from the ears;
4. Screen and clean the stripped rice to remove impurities and incomplete grains;
5. Store the cleaned rice for subsequent processing or sale.
With correct harvesting and handling methods, the quality and preservation of rice can be ensured.

